  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Development and distribution of cap-type ceramic water purifiers to solve drinking water problems in Vietnam&apos;s rural areas and reduce carbon emissions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drinking water problems are prevalent in rural areas in Vietnam. To solve this problem, we developed the first cap type ceramic water purifier &apos;hope tap&apos;. The method of using the product is simple. Many Vietnamese residents use 20 to 30 liters of water bottles when moving water. Combine the &apos;Hope Tap&apos; instead of the cap to this water bottle. After that, when the water bottle is laid to the side, it becomes a water purifier that makes clean water. Hope tap is superior to other existing solutions in terms of usability, price, and sustainability. The invention and distribution of products will greatly help solve drinking water problems, reduce carbon emissions, and protect forests in developing countries.</narrative>
  </description>
